Over the years, we have expanded to become a leading regional bank in the Northeast with over $25 billion in assets and 176 banking centers from greater New York City to Boston. Today, we offer the full range of financial services, delivered by close to 3,000 employees. But while we have grown, our core values have remained unchanged. We still put people first -- acting with responsibility, respect, ethical behavior, citizenship and teamwork. We call these principles The Webster Way. They bring us together, set us apart, and create an unshakeable core that is unique to Webster.

Franchise.Name: Atasun Optik
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Our goal is to deliver the best quality of vision in the optical sector to everybody with the best prices and to become the most preferred retail company. At Atasun Optik, we guarantee our customers satisfaction with our economic prices.

Franchise.Name: Autogrill
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Autogrill is an Italian-based catering company

Franchise.Name: Ballantynes
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Ballantynes is a Christchurch icon and has been around since 1872. It’s the perfect place to buy New Zealand souvenirs together with a selection of quality gifts.

Franchise.Name: Barbeque Nation
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The pioneers of live-grills and saucy appetizers in India have come a long way to bring the taste every mouth craves.

Franchise.Name: Barburrito
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Barburrito is a British chain of Mexican style fast food restaurants, focusing primarily on burritos. As of June 2017, the chain operates 21 stores across eleven towns and cities in the United Kingdom,

Franchise.Name: Barnes & Noble
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Barnes & Noble, Inc., a Fortune 500 company, is the bookseller with the largest number of retail outlets in the United States, and a retailer of content, digital media, and educational products.

Franchise.Name: Bartell Drugs
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Bartell Drugs is a family-owned chain of pharmacies in the Puget Sound area of the U.S. state of Washington

Franchise.Name: Baskin-Robbins
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Baskin-Robbins is the world's largest chain of ice cream specialty shop restaurants. Based in Canton, Massachusetts, it was founded in 1945 by Burt Baskin and Irv Robbins in Glendale, California.

Franchise.Name: Baydöner
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Turkish cheap but hearty doner kebab franchise

Franchise.Name: Beard Papa’s
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Since it first opened its doors in Fukuoka, Japan back in 1999, Beard Papa’s has remained committed to its pursuit of delivering uncompromising quality in every one of its doughy creations. Delight in its natural cream puffs, served fresh, every day, across our 367 stores worldwide.

Franchise.Name: Bed Bath and Beyond
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Bed Bath & Beyond Inc. is an American-owned chain of domestic merchandise retail stores in the United States, Puerto Rico, Canada and Mexico.

Franchise.Name: Bee Cheng Hiang
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Starting as a market stall in 1933 in Singapore, Bee Cheng Hiang produces Asian-style foodstuffs, especially that of Singaporean cuisine. Today, the company has expanded its operations to more than 260 retail outlets located across nine territories—China, Hong Kong, Indonesia, Macau, Malaysia, the Philippines, South Korea, Singapore and Taiwan

Franchise.Name: Bembos
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Bembos is a Peruvian fast food chain offering hamburgers, often with Peruvian-influenced variations.

Franchise.Name: Ben & Jerry's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Originally began as a small ice cream shop in Vermont, now one of the world's largest ice cream shop chains.

Franchise.Name: Ben's Cookies
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Ben’s Cookies is a chain of shops in England and elsewhere that bakes and sells chewy biscuits. It was founded in 1983 by Helge Rubinstein and co-founded by Karen Brooke Barnett.

Franchise.Name: Best Buy
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Shop Best Buy for electronics, computers, appliances, cell phones, video games & more new tech.

Franchise.Name: Best of Barbados Gift Shop
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Best of Barbados Gift Shop is an established family business, with 5 super gift shops on the island. We pride ourselves in providing our customers with distinctive merchandise that is made or designed in Barbados — and a happy shopping environment with a warm, friendly Bajan smile.

Franchise.Name: Beymen
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: A Turkish luxury clothing brand.

Franchise.Name: Big Bite Submarines
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Big Bite Submarines is a Norwegian fastfood franchise focusing on fresh subs, wraps and salads. The first restaurant was opened in 1997

Franchise.Name: Big Rooster
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Big Rooster is a chain of fast food restaurants in Papua New Guinea that specialises in roast chicken. The company began operations in 1987

Franchise.Name: Bijoux Terner
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Bijoux Terner is a global chain of fashion retail stores with over 700 locations around the world and headquartered in Miami, Florida. Bijoux Terner has over 35 years of experience designing, sourcing, and selling fashion accessories: watches, necklaces, pashminas, scarves, handbags, ties, and travel accessories.

Franchise.Name: Bikanervala
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: We are one stop for your sweetness and happiness. Bikanervala, Sweetshop -cum- Restaurant joint in your city. We are a one of leading Food&Beverage or Restaurant name in India. Our delicious effort is to provide traditional Indian fare in the atmosphere of a modern world class eatery

Franchise.Name: Billa
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Billa is a privately owned Austrian supermarket chain owned by Germany’s REWE Group. Billa operates more than 3,600 stores across Austria, Czech Republic, Slovakia, Bulgaria, Russia and Ukraine.

Franchise.Name: BIPA
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: BIPA is a high-priced, modern drugstore for all and delights with beauty and fragrance. With more than 15,000 international branded products and own brands, BIPA offers its customers everything from make-up, fragrances, body care and household products. Founded more than 30 years ago, BIPA is today not only the most well-known company in the Austrian drugstore trade, but also the undisputed favorite company with around 3.3 million loyal regular customers.

Franchise.Name: Bob's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Bob’s is the first Brazilian fast food chain, founded in 1952 by the American Brazilian tennis champion Robert Falkenburg,

Franchise.Name: Bonchon Chicken
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Bonchon Chicken is a South Korean-based international fried chicken restaurant franchise

Franchise.Name: Book Off
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Book Off is Japan's largest chain of used bookstores. Founded in August 1991, the company has had explosive success, expanding to 866 stores throughout Japan and eight overseas locations

Franchise.Name: Bookmans
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Bookmans is the largest used book retailer based in Arizona.

Franchise.Name: Books Kinokuniya
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Books Kinokuniya is a Japanese bookstore chain operated by Kinokuniya Company Ltd. founded in 1927

Franchise.Name: Books-A-Million
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Books-A-Million owns and operates the second largest bookstore chain in the United States, operating 260 stores in 32 states.

Franchise.Name: Boost Juice
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Boost Juice Bars is an international chain of retail outlets that specialise in selling fruit juice and smoothies. Boost Juice Bars was formed in 2000 with the first store located in Adelaide, South Australia.[

Franchise.Name: Booster Juice
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Booster Juice Ltd. is Canada's largest chain of fresh juice and smoothie bars. The chain specializes in smoothies composed of a pure juice, fruit sorbet or vanilla frozen yogurt, frozen fruit, fresh yogurt and ice.

Franchise.Name: Boots
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Shop our extensive range of health and beauty products from leading brands, fragrances for her and him, gift sets and much more with Boots.

Franchise.Name: BOSS
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hugo BOSS luxury clothing

Franchise.Name: Bottega Veneta
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Bottega Veneta is an Italian luxury goods and high fashion brand house best known for its leather goods which are sold worldwide and its men's and women's ready-to-wear

Franchise.Name: BreadTalk
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Founded in 2000, the BreadTalk Group has rapidly expanded to become a distinctive household brand owner that has established its mark on the world stage with its bakery, restaurant and food atrium footprints. Today, with close to 1000 outlets in 17 locales, BreadTalk produces culinary magic for everyday recipes that you savour, uniting people with good taste around the world.

Franchise.Name: Brezelkönig
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Brezelkönig is a Swiss pretzel franchise based out of the town of Emmen. We are among the most successful retail concepts and together account for more than 270 locations, primarily in high-frequency locations

Franchise.Name: Brioche Dorée
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Brioche Dorée is a French chain of Bakery/Café restaurants founded in 1976 and originally started in Brest.

Franchise.Name: Brownies & Downies
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: A Cafe employing people with a mental disability. Slogan: Good things happen over time
Franchise.Notes: as far as i know, not found at airports (yet)

Franchise.Name: Bruna
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Bruna is a Dutch retailer operating 375 shops in the Netherlands which sells books, newspapers, magazines, stationery, computer software, and cards.

Franchise.Name: Brunet
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Brunet is a group of pharmacists in Quebec, Canada.

Franchise.Name: Bulgari
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Upscale retailer of Italian designer jewelry, watches, accessories & fragrances for men & women.

Franchise.Name: Burger Baron
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The Burger Baron name is used by several fast-food restaurants in Western Canada.

Franchise.Name: Burger Fuel
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Burger Fuel is a New Zealand burger restaurant and franchise with 88 locations in six countries

Franchise.Name: Burger King
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Burger King (BK) is an American global chain of hamburger fast food restaurants

Franchise.Name: Burgeranch
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Burgeranch is an Israelifast-food chain. In 2010, the Burgeranch chain included 107 restaurants with over 1500 employees

Franchise.Name: Burgs
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Burgs is an Indian fast food chain that mainly serves gourmet burgers including chicken, lamb, fish, prawn, beef and pork, as well as veggie burgers.

Franchise.Name: Buscemi's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: In 1989, Monroe families started heading to Buscemi’s for the best pizza in town. More than a quarter-century later, we haven’t changed a thing. Buscemi’s Pizza is still all about great food, friendly service and affordable prices – and we’re still serving up freshly-made mmmm one order at a time.

Franchise.Name: Byron Burger
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Byron is a UK restaurant chain that has a casual dining experience and focuses on Burgers.
Franchise.Notes: Not at any airport in the UK that Im aware of..

Franchise.Name: Café Coffee Day
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Café Coffee Day (CCD) is an Indian café chain with over 1500 outlets that also grows its own beans in Coffee estates in South India. With over 12,000 acres of land, it is the largest producer of coffee beans in Asia

Franchise.Name: Cafe de Coral
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Founded in 1968, the Café de Coral group opened its first Café de Coral restaurant in the Causeway Bay district of Hong Kong in 1969. Since then, the group has grown to operate over 580 separate outlets across its brands all over the world. It is the largest Chinese fast food restaurant group in Hong Kong and in the world.

Franchise.Name: Café Havanna
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Café Havanna is a chain of franchise coffee stores founded in Argentina by the Havanna manufacturing company. Café Havanna sells not only different varieties of coffee, but also the classic and popular Havanna products like alfajores, lemon cookies, brownies, cakes and other chocolate and dulce de leche desserts.

Franchise.Name: Café Rembrandt
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: This is a typical local bar

Franchise.Name: Caffé Nero
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Caffè Nero is a European style coffee house brand with its headquarters in London. Currently, the company runs more than 825 coffee houses worldwide and is established in eight countries: the UK, Ireland, Poland, Cyprus, Croatia, Turkey, the UAE, and the United States

Franchise.Name: Caffè Ritazza
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: At Caffè Ritazza, our aim is simple, to bring to busy travellers great coffee, freshly made food, in a space that is uncluttered and where the service is efficient and friendly.

Franchise.Name: Çağdaş
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Çağdaş is a supermarket chain that is "both good quality and affordable" in the real sense. It feels finesse and provides the development of local flavors. Healthy, high quality and safe products offer a wide range of products in clear and spacious well-lit stores aimed at conscious consumers.

Franchise.Name: California Burrito Co.
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: California Burrito Co. is a fast food restaurant chain that specializes in burritos. It was started by Jordan Metzner, Sam Nadler and Chris Burns in 2006 in Buenos Aires.

Franchise.Name: California Fried Chicken
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: California Fried Chicken is an Indonesian fast food restaurant chain, serving principally fried chicken. Its major competitors are Texas Chicken and KFC and as of June 2011 it runs 215 locations across Indonesia.

Franchise.Name: CAPI - The Travellers Electronics Company
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: With more than 55 years of experience, Capi - The Travellers Electronics Company - is a leader in airport retailing. With over 25 shops in five countries we offer a portfolio of electronics aimed at the demanding traveller.

Franchise.Name: Captain Submarine
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Captain Submarine is a Canadian fast-food restaurant chain whose menu is highlighted by submarine sandwiches.

Franchise.Name: Caribou Coffee
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Caribou Coffee is a Minnesota-based company that specializes in espresso beverages, its own coffee blends, tea, sandwiches and bakery goods. There are more than 273 company-owned coffeehouses in 18 states and the District of Columbia, as well as 203 franchise locations in 10 countries.

Franchise.Name: Cartier
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Cartier – Fine watches, jewelry, wedding and engagement rings, leather goods and other luxury goods from the famous French brand of exclusive goods.

Franchise.Name: Casey’s General Stores
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Through the years, Casey’s success has been attributed to our clean stores and friendly employees who pride themselves in customer service. Casey’s customers have come to know us for our helpful employees, clean stores and wide selection of freshly prepared food items. With over 2,000 locations (and counting), your local Casey’s is always just around the corner.

Franchise.Name: Cave Shepherd
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Cave Shepherd is a Barbados-based retailer formed in 1906 as a partnership between two men, Messrs Cave and Shepherd. For several decades, the company itself retailed goods to both locals and tourists from its flagship store on Broad Street.

Franchise.Name: Celesio
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Celesio AG is a German healthcare and pharmaceutical company, based in Stuttgart.

Franchise.Name: Cervecería 100 Montaditos
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Cervecería 100 Montaditos is a restaurant chain in Spain specializing in sandwiches. The chain had over 350 retail stores in Spain.

Franchise.Name: Chanel
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Enter the world of CHANEL and discover the latest in Fashion & Accessories, Eyewear, Fragrance, Skincare & Makeup, Fine Jewellery & Watches.

Franchise.Name: Chefette
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Chefette Restaurants is the largest fast food restaurant chain based in the Caribbean island nation of Barbados. Currently operating throughout the island in 14 locations, Chefette is known for its broasted chicken meals as well as a local curried-'meat + vegetable' (similar to the European Gyro) roll-up or wrap, locally known as a roti.

Franchise.Name: Chez Ashton
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Chez Ashton is a popular fast food restaurant in Quebec, Canada famous for its poutine.

Franchise.Name: Chicken Cottage
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Chicken Cottage International is a UK-based fast food chain. The company is the master franchisor and owner of the "Chicken Cottage" brand.

Franchise.Name: Chicken Licken
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Chicken Licken is a South African fast-foodfried chicken restaurant chain.[4] The company had an 80% share of South Africa's fast food market in 2010, tying with McDonald's

Franchise.Name: Chicken Treat
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Chicken Treat is an Australian barbecue chicken fast food restaurant chain, currently operating 60 locations.

Franchise.Name: Chick-fil-A
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Chick-fil-A is an American fast food restaurant chain headquartered in the Atlanta district of College Park, Georgia, specializing in chicken sandwiches

Franchise.Name: Chili Beans
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Chilli Beans began its activities in the late 90's, under the command of the businessman Caito Maia. Almost 17 years later, and today consolidated as the largest specialized network of sunglasses and accessories in Latin America, the company has more than 740 points of sale, including Brazil, Portugal, United States, Colombia, Kuwait, Peru, Abu Dhabi, Mexico , Chile and Thailand.

Franchise.Name: Chili's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Chili's Grill & Bar is an American casual dining restaurant chain that features Tex-Mex-style cuisine

Franchise.Name: China Nepstar
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: China Nepstar Chain Drugstore is China's largest retail drugstore chain on the number of directly operated stores.

Franchise.Name: Chowking
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Chowking is a Philippine-based restaurant chain. The concept combines Western fast food service with Chinese food menu.

Franchise.Name: Churromania
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Churromania, based in Miami, Florida, is a Venezuelan chain of Churro stores founded by Ariel Acosta Rubio and his wife, Maria Alejandra Bravo, in 1997

Franchise.Name: Cinnabon
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Cinnabon is an American chain of baked goods stores and kiosks. The company’s signature item is a cinnamon roll. As of December 2017, over 1,200 Cinnabon bakeries were operating in 48 countries.

Franchise.Name: Circle-K
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Circle K has become one of the most widely recognized convenience store brands, known worldwide for quality products and great customer service. We have come a long way since our humble beginnings, and we’re proud of where we’ve been and where we’re going.

Franchise.Name: Coffee Culture
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Coffee Culture offers great coffee, delicious food and a whole lotta love!

Franchise.Name: Coffee House
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Coffee House - the largest network of coffee houses in Russia. Our coffee houses are always near and they are ideal for meetings and communication, work and leisure. We are open and positive, energetic and hospitable. The cup of our coffee sets the rhythm for the whole day.

Franchise.Name: Coffee Time
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Coffee Time is a chain of Canadian coffee shops. The company is a competitor of the Tim Hortons chain in the Greater Toronto Area. It is headquartered in Scarborough, Ontario.

Franchise.Name: Coffeemania
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Coffeemania is a Moscow based restaurant chain which was established in 2001.Over these years Coffeemania has become a part of everyday life for thousands of our guests. Coffeemania perfectly combines a warm and cozy coffee house and restaurant with an extensive menu collected from all over the world.

Franchise.Name: Coffeeshop Company
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Coffeeshop Company is an Austrian family enterprise and part of the Schärf Group of companies. It has specialized in the production of high quality Espresso coffee from highland Arabica coffee beans. Coffeeshop Company operates as a franchise based system of coffee shops in Armenia, Austria, Azerbaijan, Bulgaria, Germany, Hungary, Czech Republic, Slovakia, Poland, Turkey, Morocco, Egypt, United States, Russia, Slovenia, Croatia, Macedonia Mexico.

Franchise.Name: Cofix
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Cofix is an Israeli coffee shop, bar and supermarket chain established in 2013 by Avner “Avi” Katz. The chain has 148 branches, most of which are regular branches selling coffee, food products, and occasionally a small selection of other products. The entire chain is kosher, but in some Haredi population centers the products are additionally glatt kosher, and the branches have no seating areas.

Franchise.Name: Coles
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Coles is a Canadian bookstore chain owned by Indigo Books and Music. Coles currently serves as Indigo's brand for small-scale bookstores in locations such as shopping malls

Franchise.Name: Collezione
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: A Turkish clothing brand.

Franchise.Name: Collins Booksellers
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Collins Booksellers Pty Ltd is an Australian book store chain founded in 1922 by Frederick Henry Slamen.

Franchise.Name: Colombian Emeralds International
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Colombian Emeralds International has expanded to over 60 locations throughout the Caribbean, Central America and on-board Norwegian Cruise Lines. Today, we are one of the largest retailers in the region, offering a large selection of renowned jewelry and watch brands.

Franchise.Name: Cook Door
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Cook Door is a chain of fast food restaurants based in Cairo, Egypt. It is one of Egypt's fast food chains along with Smiley's Grill and Mo'men.

Franchise.Name: Cortés
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Cortés is a chain of rotisseries established in Brazil. In a house like Cortés, the center of attention is the ember. Fresh ingredients, recipes that bring the simplicity and strength of the countryside food. The chain has now expanded to 3 major cities in Brazil.

Franchise.Name: Costa Coffee
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Costa Coffee is a British multinational coffeehouse company headquartered in Dunstable, Bedfordshire, and a wholly owned subsidiary of Whitbread. It is the second largest coffeehouse chain in the world behind Starbucks and the largest in the UK

Franchise.Name: Country Style
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Country Style Food Services, Inc. is a fast/casual chain of coffee shops operating primarily in the Canadian province of Ontario which serves oatmeal, soup, sandwiches, salads, and coffee.

Franchise.Name: Croasonho
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Founded in 1997, with the birth of Croasonho’s recipe, the Croasonho brand has grown into the gastronomic market, standing out for handcrafted Croasonhos with crunchy dough and surprising fillings. Today there are over 70 stores in 16 Brazilian states and thousands of people in love with the brand!

Franchise.Name: Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Crystal Jade is a Singapore-based culinary brand with one Michelin star and multiple Michelin Bib Gourmand awards, with over 100 outlets across 25 major cities. Well regarded for its culinary expertise and commitment to quality, Crystal Jade’s brand mission to spread the word on Chinese cuisine and culture has remained unchanged.

Logo.File: .\Data\Images\Businesses\Franchise\Crystal Jade La Mian Xiao Long Bao.png

Franchise.Name: Crystal Media
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Crystal Media was founded in 1995. Specialized in electronics and select multimedia products, with stores in airports and international commercial areas as well as online sales. We expose a differentiated offer by brands where each of them can present their best products.

Franchise.Name: Culver's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Culver Franchising System, Inc., doing business as Culver's, is a privately owned and operated fast casual restaurant chain that operates primarily in the Midwestern United States

Franchise.Name: CVS Health
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: CVS Health Corporation is an American retail pharmacy and health care company headquartered in Woonsocket, Rhode Island.

Franchise.Name: D&R
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: A Turkish general store which sells magazines, CDs, DVDs, and other electronic items.

Franchise.Name: Dairy Queen
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Dairy Queen, often abbreviated DQ, is a chain of soft serve ice cream and fast-food restaurants

Franchise.Name: Daunt Books
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Daunt Books is a chain of bookshops in London, founded by James Daunt. It traditionally specialised in travel books.

Franchise.Name: dean&david
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Since 2007 the Munich-based company dean&david has been offering fast, healthy and entirely fresh cuisine. The company now has more than 70 outlets in Germany, Switzerland, Austria and Luxembourg.

Franchise.Name: Delhaize
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Delhaize Le Lion / De Leeuw is a food retailer headquartered in Sint-Jans-Molenbeek, Brussels, Belgium, and operating in seven countries and on three continents. The principal activity of Delhaize Group is the operation of food supermarkets.

Franchise.Name: Delifrance
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Délifrance is a bakery company that serves “French style” bakery products in over 50 countries on five continents. Its restaurants serve “French style” baked products such as croissants, gâteaux, fougasses, pains au chocolat, brioches, crisp praline, and baguettes.

Franchise.Name: Demel
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Demel is a famous pastry shop and chocolaterie established in 1786 in Vienna, Austria. The company bears the title of a Purveyor to the Imperial and Royal Court up to today.

Franchise.Name: Derimod
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Derimod is a Turkish leather goods producer and retailer, with stores in the US as well as in Turkey.

Franchise.Name: Desa
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Desa is a Turkish leather goods producer and retailer.

Franchise.Name: DFS
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: DFS is a network of duty free shops operating in several countries across Asia Pacific and Oceania.

Franchise.Name: Diamonds International
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Diamonds International was established over thirty years ago. What began as one store in St. Thomas has now blossomed into more than 125 locations. Diamonds International is one of the largest jewelry retailers in the world. We have more locations in the Caribbean, Mexico, and Alaska than any other fine jeweler, with the company’s headquarters in New York City.

Franchise.Name: Dic Ann's Hamburgers
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Dic Ann's Hamburgers is a fast-food restaurant chain based in the Montreal Metropolitan Area, Canada.

Franchise.Name: Dickey's Barbecue Pit
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: America's largest barbeque chain

Franchise.Name: Dicos
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Dicos is a Chinese fast-food restaurant chain owned by the Tianjin Ding Qiao Food Service. The chain ranks third among China's top three fast-food enterprises, as it has almost as many restaurants as McDonald's.

Franchise.Name: Dior
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Christian Dior SE, commonly known as Dior, is a French luxury goods company

Franchise.Name: Discount Drug Mart
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Discount Drug Mart, is an Ohio-based drug store chain that opened its first store in Elyria, Ohio in 1969.

Franchise.Name: Disney Store
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The Disney Store is an international chain of specialty stores selling only Disney related items, many of them exclusive, under its own name and Disney Outlet.

Franchise.Name: Ditsch
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Ditsch is a German chain of pretzel bars also selling croissants and pizza snacks. It operates approximately 200 outlets in Germany but over the 2010s it also traded in the United Kingdom with up to 13 outlets there at its height.

Franchise.Name: Ditt Apotek
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Ditt Apotek is a chain of 80 pharmacies owned and run by independent pharmacists on franchise from Norsk Medisinaldepot, a subsidiary of Celesio.

Franchise.Name: Dixons Travel
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Electronics, headphones, travel accessories

Franchise.Name: Dixy Chicken
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Dixy Chicken is a fast food chain that specializes in halal chicken. The company was founded by two British Pakistanis, who offered halal versions of products found in McDonald's and KFC.

Franchise.Name: Dokya
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Dokya is a Thai bookseller based in Bangkok and one of the largest bookstore chains in Thailand

Franchise.Name: Domino's Pizza
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Domino's Pizza Inc. is a large American pizza restaurant chain founded in 1960

Franchise.Name: Donut King
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Donut King is an Australian doughnut franchise, based on the Gold Coast, Queensland.

Franchise.Name: Droga Raia
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Raia S.A. operates a chain of drug stores in Brazil. The company primarily retails medicines, as well as health care, hygiene, and beauty products. As of June 30, 2011, the company operated 362 stores throughout the states of Sao Paulo, Rio de Janeiro, Minas Gerais, Parana, and Rio Grande do Sul. Raia S.A. was founded in 1905 and is headquartered in Sao Paulo, Brazil. As of November 10, 2011, Droga Raia S.A. operates as a subsidiary of Raia Drogasil SA.
Franchise.Notes: Waiting to send logo to EG0

Franchise.Name: Drogarias Farmais
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Drogarias Farmais, founded in 1994, operates and franchises a chain of drug stores in Brazil. Its stores offer drugs, medicines, pharmaceutical and dietetic products, toiletries, optical products, medical acoustics, dental and veterinary products, cosmetics and perfumes, and other related products, as well as appliances and accessories for use in therapeutic or cosmetic corrections.
Franchise.Notes: Waiting to send logo to EG0

Franchise.Name: Dubai Duty Free
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Dubai Duty Free (DDF) is the company responsible for the duty-free operations at Dubai International Airport and Al Maktoum International Airport.
Franchise.CEO: Sheikh Ahmed bin Saeed Al Maktoum

Franchise.Name: Dufry
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Dufry AG is a Swiss-based travel retailer operating around 2,200 duty-free and duty-paid shops in airports, cruise lines, seaports, railway stations and central tourist areas. Dufry employs almost 29,000 people.

Franchise.Name: Dunkin'Donuts
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Massive chain of donut/bakery shops

Franchise.Name: Dutch & Delicious
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Small local restaurant

Franchise.Name: Dymocks Booksellers
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Dymocks booksellers is an Australian founded privately owned bookstore chain, that also specialise in CDS, DVDS, Blu-ray discs, e-books and related merchandising.

Franchise.Name: Eason & Son
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Eason & Son is an Irish retail company primarily involved in the wholesale and distribution of books, newspapers, magazines, stationery and cards in Ireland

Franchise.Name: East Dawning
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: East Dawning is Yum China's fusion of the KFC business model with Chinese cuisine

Franchise.Name: Eat.
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: EAT. create, make and serve fresh food to go. As 2014 MIDAS Award Winners, EAT. take pride in the range of soup, hot pots, salads, sandwiches and drinks, they serve fresh every day.

Franchise.Name: Eataly
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Eataly is the largest Italian food hall in the world, comprising a variety of restaurants, food and beverage counters, bakery, retail items, and a cooking school.

Franchise.Name: Eddie Rocket's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Eddie Rocket’s Limited is an Irish restaurant chain, with its headquarters in Dublin.[1] It offers American-style food in 1950s' style diners.

Franchise.Name: Egon
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Egon restaurant is a Norwegian restaurant concept that opened its first restaurant on Nordstrand in Oslo in 1984. Egon is a registered trademark and owned by Norrein AS in Trondheim. In Trondheim is also the headquarters of the Egon restaurant chain.

Franchise.Name: Empik
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Empik is a Polish commercial chain selling books, international press and media products

Franchise.Name: Entrée Bakeries
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Entrée is a Frency-style artisan bakery chain based out of Georgia established in 2008. Aside from pastries, Entrée also offers an assortment of breakfast menus and soups, along with fresh juices, coffee, and tea.

Franchise.Name: Ermenegildo Zegna
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Ermenegildo Zegna is an Italian luxury fashion house that makes men’s clothing and accessories. Founded in 1910 when Ermenegildo bought his father’s textile looms, it is now managed by the fourth generation of the Zegna family and remains in family ownership.

Franchise.Name: Es Teler 77
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Business description: Established in 1982’s Jakarta, Es Teler 77 has grown to become a successful regional phenomenon, with 200 stores in Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore, and Australia. Es Teler 77 serves many other classic and delicious Indonesian dishes, along with its signature ‘Es Teler’.

Franchise.Name: Eslite Bookstore
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Eslite Bookstore is one of the largest retail bookstore chains in Taiwan. It also provides one of the largest English language publications and translation materials in Taiwan.

Franchise.Name: Espresso House
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Founded in 1996. What started as a small café in Lund, Sweden has grown to be the Nordic Region's largest coffee-shop chain. Inspired by Italian coffee culture and American coffee tradition.

Franchise.Name: Esprit
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Esprit Holdings Limited is a publicly owned manufacturer of clothing, footwear, accessories, jewellery and housewares under the Esprit label.

Franchise.Name: Etos
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Etos B.V., trading as Etos, was founded in 1918 by Philips to create a grocery and drugstore where Philips employees could benefit from lower priced products than the average stores. 'Etos' is an abbreviation for the Dutch words: Eendracht, Toewijding, Overleg and Samenwerking (Unity, Devotion, Consultation and Cooperation).

Franchise.Name: Excelso
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Excelso is an original coffee shop from Indonesia and a part of Kapal Api Group, the largest coffee producer in Indonesia. Excelso has grown to become one of the strongest and recognized coffee shop brands in Indonesia. More than a decade later, it has now becomes a chain with up to 100 stores in around 28 cities in Indonesia.

Franchise.Name: Exclusive Books
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Exclusive Books is one of South Africa's largest bookselling chains with stores throughout South Africa

Franchise.Name: EXKi
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: EXKi is an international chain of healthy fast-casual "grab-and-go" restaurants. The Belgian owners have stated that the name is a play on the French word "exquis", meaning "exquisite" or "delightful".

Franchise.Name: Extreme Pita
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Extreme Pita is a Canadian-based fast-casual chain, owned by MTY Group. Headquartered in Richmond Hill, Ontario, the company has more than 175 units throughout Canada and the United States.

Franchise.Name: Faasos
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Faasos is an Indian 'food on demand' company that was incorporated in 2011.

Franchise.Name: FabIndia
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Retailing garments, furnishings, fabrics and ethnic products handmade by craftspeople across rural India

Franchise.Name: Fairwood
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Fairwood is a fast food chain offering Chinese and Western food. Founded in December 1972 in the Tsuen Wan district of Hong Kong,

Franchise.Name: Falke
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Since 1895, the Falke family business has stood for fashionable clothing made from high-quality materials, finished with handcrafted perfection and an eye for detail. Falke has gone international with stores in Germany, Switzerland, Netherlands and Belgium.

Franchise.Name: Familiprix
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Familiprix is a Canadian group of independent pharmacists. As of 2012, Familiprix consists of 320 pharmacies with over $1 billion in retail sales.

Franchise.Name: Famous Dave's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Famous Dave's of America is a chain of barbecue restaurants serving pork ribs, chicken, beef brisket, and several flavors of barbecue sauce

Franchise.Name: FAO Schwarz
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: FAO Schwarz, founded in 1862, was once the oldest toy store in the United States. The company is known for its unique high-end toys, life-sized stuffed animals, dolls, and games.

Franchise.Name: Farmacias Benavides
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Farmacias Benavides is a Mexican drugstore chain.

Franchise.Name: Farmacity
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Farmacity is a protagonist in the field of health in Argentina thanks to the dedication of our experienced pharmaceutical technical directors and their specialized teams.

Franchise.Name: Fast Eddies
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Fast Eddie's is a burger franchise started in Brantford, Ontario, Canada in 1987 and focused on drive through and walk up service only. Currently Fast Eddie's operates in five Ontario cities with eight different locations and serves a variety of typical fast food with notable, relatively unique items like the Crazy Fry.

Franchise.Name: Fast Eddys
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Fast Eddys is a fast food and restaurant chain operating in Perth, Western Australia and formerly in Adelaide, South Australia and Melbourne, Victoria.

Franchise.Name: Fiero
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: FIERO is a trademark that is found in the supply of products as well as in fixed operations. The various products in the menu are sold at many different retail points in the market.

Franchise.Name: First Kitchen
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: First Kitchen is a Japanese fast food restaurant chain operated by First Kitchen Co., Ltd., a wholly owned subsidiary of Suntory Holdings.

Franchise.Name: Flunch
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Flunch is a French cafeteria-style fast casual restaurant chain that is owned by the Agapes Restauration group

Franchise.Name: Fnac
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Fnac is a large French retail chain selling cultural and electronic products, founded by André Essel and Max Théret in 1954.

Franchise.Name: Fondo de Cultura Económica
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Fondo de Cultura Económica is a Spanish language, non-profit publishing group, partly founded by the Mexican government. It is based in Mexico but it has subsidiaries throughout the Spanish-speaking world.

Franchise.Name: Foyles
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Foyles is a bookseller with a chain of seven stores in England.

Franchise.Name: Frango Assado
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The story of Frango Assado starts in 1952 when the couple José and Rosa Mamprin opened a small fruit stand on the edge of the newly inaugurated Anhanguera Highway, a road linking the city of São Paulo to the interior. The business started as a small fruit bank today is part of a food giant operating in Brazil, Panama, Dominican Republic, Colombia, Puerto Rico and Mexico.

Franchise.Name: Frank Pepe Pizzeria Napolenta
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Started in 1925 in New Haven CT. Nationally known as one of the worlds best pizza's, and now has nine locations in and around CT

Franchise.Name: Frasses Hamburgers
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Frasses Hamburgers is a Swedish hamburger chain. The first Frasses restaurant was opened in 1975 in Luleå

Franchise.Name: Fred's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Fred’s operates in 15 states in the southeastern United States with 304 full-service pharmacy departments

Franchise.Name: Freshii
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Freshii is a Canadian fast casual restaurant franchise that serves burritos, wraps, soups, salads, and frozen yogurt. It was founded in 2005 by CEO Matthew Corrin.

Franchise.Name: Freshness Burger
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Freshness Burger is a fast food restaurant from Japan. Founded in 1992, it sells hamburgers, sandwiches, salads, and coffee drinks.

Franchise.Name: Frey Wille
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Frey Wille, formerly “Michaela Frey Emaillemanufaktur”, is an enamel jewellery manufacturer based in Vienna, Austria founded in 1951. The label is known for its hand decorated designs that are based on the works of 19th and 20th century artists.

Franchise.Name: Fryer's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Fryer's is an international fast food chain focused on Hamburgers, Fried Chicken, French fries, and Milkshakes. Its headquarters in the Richmond, BC area. It is currently owned and operated by Fryer's International, Inc.

Franchise.Name: Ganzee
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Cave Shepherd & Co. Limited together with its partner African Propriety (Holdings) Inc. operates Ganzee, a leading destination souvenir retail operation in the islands of Barbados and Grenada. Ganzee shops offer a wide range of quality souvenir items ranging from apparel such as hats, caps and t-shirts to gifting and home-wares.

Franchise.Name: Giraffas
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Giraffas is a Brazilian fast-food chain founded in August 1981 by two friends, Mauro Lacerda and Muniz Neto. Its first store located in Brazil's capital city, Brasília. In 1991, the chain began franchising, and it has since expanded across Brazil. It has also opened in Paraguay and in Miami in the U.S.

Franchise.Name: Global Culture
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Global Culture is a New Zealand company that supports a range of artists around New Zealand that design and create an inspired range of gifts, pottery and jewellery

Franchise.Name: Glorious Britain
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: British themed souvenirs

Franchise.Name: GNC
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: GNC Holdings is a Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania-based American company selling health and nutrition related products, including vitamins, supplements, minerals, herbs, sports nutrition, diet, and energy products.

Franchise.Name: Goldilocks Bakeshop
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Goldilocks Bakeshop is a bakeshop chain based in the Philippines, which produces and distributes Philippine cakes and pastries.

Franchise.Name: Goli Vada Pav
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Goli Vada Pav is an Indian ethnic fast food restaurant chain originated from Mumbai, Maharashtra, India. It was founded in 2004 as a vadapav restaurant by Venkatesh Iyer and Shivadas Menon

Franchise.Name: Goody's Burger House
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Goody's Burger House S.A. is Greece's largest fast food company.

Franchise.Name: Gordon Ramseys Plane Food
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Fine Dining British Cuisine

Franchise.Name: Gordons Chemist
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Gordons Chemists is a chain of more than 60 pharmacies, located in the UK.

Franchise.Name: Grand Café Plaza
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Small local restaurant

Franchise.Name: Greggs
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Greggs is the largest bakery chain in the United Kingdom. It specialises in savoury products such as pasties, sausage rolls and sandwiches and sweet items including doughnuts and vanilla slices.

Franchise.Name: Griletto
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Since its conception, Griletto has won numerous awards and acknowledgements from magazines and business associations in the category of fast food. Today, Griletto is Brazil’s largest grilling network and one of the fastest growing brands in the country in an equally prolific and competitive segment.

Franchise.Name: G-Star
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: G-Star is a Dutch designer clothing company, founded by Jos van Tilburg in Amsterdam in 1989, which produces urban clothing

Franchise.Name: Gunung Agung
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Gunung Agung is one of Indonesia's leading bookstore companies. It is named after the volcano of that name in Bali, Indonesia.

Franchise.Name: Guzman y Gomez
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Guzman y Gomez is an Australian licensed, casual-dining restaurant chain specialising in authentic Mexican dishes such as burritos, nachos, taco, quesadillas and other specialty items.

Franchise.Name: H&M
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hennes & Mauritz AB is a Swedish multinational clothing-retail company, known for its fast-fashion clothing for men, women, teenagers and children.

Franchise.Name: H.D. İskender
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Turkish luxurious iskender kebab brand

Franchise.Name: Habib's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Habib's is a Brazilian fast food company that specialises in Middle Eastern cuisine and Brazilian sandwiches. It has more than 475 outlets

Franchise.Name: Hacıoğlu
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hacıoğlu started his taste journey in 1965 in this small shop, where the Hacıoğlu family presents traditional flavors. This initiative, initiated by Hacıoğlu family elders, led to this small shop becoming a food giant with 100% Turkish capital.

Franchise.Name: Haldirams
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Haldiram's has its roots established in 1937 in the form of a small retail Sweet & Namkeen shop in Bikaner,

Franchise.Name: Half Price Books
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Half Price Books is the largest family-owned chain of new and used bookstores in the United States. The company’s original motto is "We buy and sell anything printed or recorded except yesterday's newspaper",

Franchise.Name: Hamburguesas El Corral
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hamburguesas El Corral is a Colombian restaurant chain with more than 208 locations.

Franchise.Name: Happy Seafood
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Small local seafood restaurant

Franchise.Name: Hardee's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hardee's Food Systems, Inc., is an American-based fast-food restaurant chain with locations primarily in the Southern and Midwestern United States

Franchise.Name: Harry Ramsden's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Harry Ramsden's is a fast food restaurant chain based in the United Kingdom which offers fish and chips and assorted themed dishes. The business has 45 owned and franchised outlets throughout the UK and Ireland and serves around four million meals annually

Franchise.Name: Harvey's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Harvey's is a fast food restaurant chain that operates in Canada, with locations in every province. It serves hamburgers, hot dogs, french fries, onion rings, and other other traditional fast-food fares..

Franchise.Name: Havaianas
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Havaianas was founded in 1962 by Scotsman Robert Fraser as the first mass produced rubber flip flops. Now, Havaianas flip-flops are the most popular in the world, with 200 million pairs being sold every year.

Franchise.Name: Havakshop
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: At the HavakShop stores where model aircraft, key chains, flight socks, radiation absorbing t-shirts and many aviation products and gift items are sold; products are also sold for the professional needs that members are difficult to supply.

Franchise.Name: Hazer Baba
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: With roots as a small family business in 1888, Hazer Baba today is one of the most well-known Turkish brand in more than 40 countries, single-handedly producing the majority of all Turkish delight exports in the world. In addition to Turkish delight, Hazer Baba is also a reputable producer and exporter of instant fruit teas (in powder form). Cotton Candy Delight, Halva assortments in fancy gift boxes, high-end Turkish Coffee and Turkish Black Tea blends, luxury Candied Chestnuts are among our other exports.

Franchise.Name: Heinemann
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Shop on a budget with HEINEMANN Duty Free at Airports — international brands at low prices!

Franchise.Name: Helixir Smoothies Bar
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Small local smoothies bar

Franchise.Name: HEMA
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: HEMA originally an acronym for Hollandsche Eenheidsprijzen Maatschappij Amsterdam, 'Hollandic Standard Prices Company Amsterdam' is a Dutch discount retail chain that started life as a dimestore

Franchise.Name: Henry
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Henry is a new, personal form of eating out restaurant established in Vienna, Austria. Henry prides itself on freshly prepared dishes that the customers selects themselves at the buffet or served by the portion from deli counters. Customers at Henry can expect fresh premium cuisine for a quick snack on the go and at home.

Franchise.Name: Herfy
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Herfy is a major fast food restaurant chain in Saudi Arabia and one of the largest in the Middle East, surpassing international chains in terms of presence.

Franchise.Name: Hermès
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: In the library of Hermès perfumes, every creation tells a story, opens up an imaginary world.

Franchise.Name: Hero Certified Burgers
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hero Certified Burgers is a Canadian restaurant chain franchise that sells hamburgers and other quick service restaurant fare. It is based in Toronto, Ontario, Canada and was founded in 2004.

Franchise.Name: Hesburger
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hesburger is a fast food chain based in Turku, Finland.[1][2] Today, it is the largest hamburger restaurant chain in Finland,

Franchise.Name: Higginbotham's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Higginbotham's is an Indian bookstore chain and publisher based in the city of Chennai.

Franchise.Name: Hillbilly's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hillbilly's as it is more commonly known, is an Irish-owned fast-food restaurant chain with restaurants located across Ireland. The restaurant chain specializes in fried chicken and poultry products.

Franchise.Name: HokBen
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hokben is a Japanese fast food chain of restaurants based in Jakarta, Indonesia. Their chain of restaurants today spread across Java and Bali.

Franchise.Name: Hosta Piknik
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Turkish cheap take away kebab brand

Franchise.Name: Hot Topic
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hot Topic is an American retail chain specializing in counterculture-related clothing and accessories, as well as licensed music.

Franchise.Name: Hotto Motto
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hotto Motto is a Japanese fast food chain specializing in take out bento, found in all but 5 of Japan's 47 prefectures. It is owned by Plenus, which operates out of the Kyushu-Yamaguchi region.

Franchise.Name: Hudson Group
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hudson Group, one of the largest travel retailers in North America

Franchise.Name: Hudson News
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Chain of newsstands in airports around the United States

Franchise.Name: Hugendubel
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hugendubel is one of two major book retailers in Germany. It was founded in 1893 by Heinrich Karl Gustav Hugendubel in Munich.

Franchise.Name: Hungry Jacks
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hungry Jack's Pty Ltd is the exclusive Australian master fast food franchise of Burger King Corporation. It is a wholly owned subsidiary of Competitive Foods Australia, a privately held company owned by Jack Cowin.

Franchise.Name: Hunt Brothers Pizza
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hunt Brothers Pizza is an American food chain

Franchise.Name: IHOP
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Since 1958, IHOP has been the place where people connect over breakfast, enjoy study breaks, grab a bite before or after sporting events, and so much more. And no matter what menu items they order, there’s one ingredient that’s always constant — a smile. We’ve seen millions of smiles over the years in our restaurants, and now shared in photos across our social properties. In fact, smiles are so much a part of our culture that we changed our logo to include one.

Franchise.Name: Indigo Books and Music
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Indigo Books & Music Inc., usually known as "Indigo" and stylized "!ndigo", is Canada's largest book, gift and specialty toy retailer, operating stores in all ten provinces and one territory, and through a website offering a selection of books, toys, home décor, stationery and gifts.

Franchise.Name: In-N-Out Burger
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: In-N-Out Burger is an American regional chain of fast food restaurants with locations primarily in the American Southwest and Pacific coast.

Franchise.Name: J.CO Donuts
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: J.CO Donuts & Coffee is a cafe restaurant chain originating from Indonesia that specializes in donuts, coffee and frozen yogurt. The company is owned and managed by Johnny Andrean Group.

Franchise.Name: Jamin
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: National candy chain

Franchise.Name: JD Sports
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: JD sports and trainers

Franchise.Name: Jean Coutu Group
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Jean Coutu Group is a Canadian drugstore chainheadquartered in Varennes, Quebec since 2017

Franchise.Name: Jet's Pizza
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Jet's Pizza is an American pizza franchise restaurant

Franchise.Name: Jimmy John's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Jimmy John's Franchise, LLC is a franchised sandwich restaurant chain, specializing in delivery.

Franchise.Name: Jin Jin Wok
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Jin Jin opened its first franchise still as Chinese cuisine. Over the years, it has decided to move to a more sophisticated and comprehensive cuisine, privileging the coexistence of customers in their spaces, sheltering the concept of Asian cuisine. Today there are more than 70 stores spread throughout Brazil, it is present in 10 states.

Franchise.Name: Joint Publishing
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Joint Publishing is a book store chain and publisher founded at Queen's Road Central in Hong Kong

Franchise.Name: Joker
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Joker provides the best quality products at the best prices. Moreover, we are always with you on our internet site and our stores increasing in number day by day.

Franchise.Name: Jollibee
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Asia's answer to USA's McDonalds, Jollibee has quickly grown to become a large multinational fast food operator.

Franchise.Name: Juice Planet
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Our entrepreneurial trial began with a small kiosk in Izmir in 2009 to share the knowledge about healty eating, by developing products, the concept and consumer chanelles has become a large organization.

Franchise.Name: Julius Meinl
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Julius Meinl is a leading coffee company in Austria, Italy, Central, and Eastern Europe. The company operates in over 70 countries with over 650 employees worldwide. Its business focuses on coffee, tea and fruit preserves with coffee being the most important category.

Franchise.Name: Jumbo King
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Jumbo King is a chain of fast food restaurants based primarily in Mumbai, specialising in the Maharashtrian regional dish vada pav.

Franchise.Name: KaatiZone
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: KaatiZone is a Bangalore-based chain of Indian fast-food restaurants specializing in Kati Rolls. Founded by Kiran Nadkarni in 2004, the restaurant is famous for its Chicken Tikka and Mixed Veg Rolls.

Franchise.Name: Kantin
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Turkish cheap snack buffet

Franchise.Name: Kebab Turki Baba Rafi
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Kebab Turki Baba Rafi is the world's largest chain of kebab, which operates more than 1,200 outlets[1] in Indonesia, Malaysia, Philippines and Bangladesh. Headquartered in Indonesia.

Franchise.Name: KFC
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Fried Chicken fast food restuarant

Franchise.Name: Khaan Buuz
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Khaanbuuz Co Ltd is Mongolia's largest fast-food chain. Although they specialise in Mongolian national foods, in particular buuz dumplings, Khaanbuuz also serves some foods influenced from Korea and Russia.

Franchise.Name: Kinney Drugs
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Kinney Drugs is a chain of over 110 drugstores and pharmacies throughout Central and Northern New York, as well as Vermont. Its headquarters is located in Gouverneur.

Franchise.Name: KKDK Luggage
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: KKDK puts a major focus on high-quality bags. In the shop, the staff can help you find what you’re looking for among a wide selection of luggage, briefcases, computer bags, handbags, backpacks and wallets. Along with the KKDK brand, you’ll find well-known quality brands such as Rimowa, Samsonite, Tumi, Mandarina Duck and Victorinox.

Franchise.Name: Klenger Burger
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Klenger Burger is an Indonesian restaurant chain based in Jakarta, operated by PT Kinarya Anak Negeri. The restaurant chain served halal hamburgers designed to suit the Indonesian palate.

Franchise.Name: Kochlöffel
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Kochlöffel is a German fast-food restaurant chain. Its product range includes hamburgers, chicken, bratwurst, currywurst and french fries with their signature turquoise plastic fork resembling a cooking spoon.

Franchise.Name: Koni Store
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Koni Store is a Brazilian chain of Japanese food headquartered in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.

Franchise.Name: Koorong
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Koorong is a Christian bookstore chain operating across Australia. It is the largest retailer of Christian books and media in Australia.

Franchise.Name: Kotipizza
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Kotipizza Oyj is the largest pizza restaurant chain in the Nordic countries. Its head office is in Helsinki, Finland. Kotipizza was founded in 1987 in Vaasa, Finland.

Franchise.Name: Kroshka Kartoshka
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: “Kroshka Kartoshka” is a well-known Russian chain of fast food restaurants, developing its unique format of dishes based on baked potatoes with a variety of mouth-watering fillers. Today, three hundred restaurants are open all over Russia, located both on the food courts of shopping centers and in freestanding buildings with the network expanding also in the CIS countries, Eastern and Western Europe.

Franchise.Name: Kudu
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Kudu is a large fast food chain in Saudi Arabia. Kudu was established in 1988 and has over 300 branches in Saudi Arabia.

Franchise.Name: Kura Zushi
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Kura zushi is a sushi restaurant chain located in Japan. It has 362 locations in Japan, and a few more outside Japan. While it is a conveyor belt sushi chain, it relies on a high level of automation allowing the average location to function with fifteen to twenty staff members.

Franchise.Name: Kyobo Book Centre
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Kyobo Book Centre is the largest bookstore chain in South Korea. It has ten stores in seven cities

Franchise.Name: Kyochon
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Kyochon F&B Co., Ltd. is a South Korean fried chicken restaurant chain. Founded in 1991, Kyochon is one of the largest Korean fried chicken restaurants in South Korea

Franchise.Name: La Belle Province
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: La Belle Province is a well-known fast food restaurant chain in the province of Quebec, Canada.

Franchise.Name: La Feltrinelli
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Feltrinelli is an Italian publishing company founded in 1954 by Giangiacomo Feltrinelli.

Franchise.Name: La Place
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: La Place is a Dutch restaurant chain, owned by Jumbo (taken over from the bankrupt department store giant V&D)

Franchise.Name: La Porchetta
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: La Porchetta /por'ket:a/ is an Australian and New Zealand restaurant franchise which has become one of the biggest Italian restaurant chains in these nations.

Franchise.Name: Lacoste
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Fashionwear and sporting goods

Franchise.Name: Lafleur Restaurants
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Lafleur Restaurants is a chain of family-owned fast food restaurants located in the greater Montreal area.

Franchise.Name: Lawtons
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Lawtons is a Canadian drug store chain owned by the Sobeys Group of Stellarton, Nova Scotia with a head office located in Dartmouth, Nova Scotia.

Franchise.Name: Le Pain Français
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The first Le Pain Français Café opened in Gothenburg, Sweden, by french immigrants in 1995. The vision was to create a french café with a bakery and patisserie. Today it's one of swedens most loved cafés.

Franchise.Name: Leon Restaurants
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Leon is a fast food restaurant chain based in the United Kingdom founded in 2004.

Franchise.Name: Libraff
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: A recent newcomer to the book chain in Azerbaijan, Libraff is founded by Taleh Heydarov, son of the esteemed minister Kamaleddin Heydarov. Libraff has grown to become a major key player and competitor in the book retail industry.

Franchise.Name: Lids
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Hat World Inc. is an American retailer specializing in athletic headwear. It primarily operates under the LIDS and Hat World brands with stores in the U.S., Puerto Rico and Canada.

Franchise.Name: Lifestyle
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Lifestyle stores sell Indian and western apparel, footwear, handbags, beauty products and fashion accessories for men, women and children

Franchise.Name: LifeWay Christian Resources
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: LifeWay Christian Resources, based in Nashville, Tennessee, is one of the largest providers of religious and Christian resources in the world

Franchise.Name: Little Caesars
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Little Caesars is the third-largest pizza chain in the United States, behind Pizza Hut and Domino's Pizza. It operates and franchises pizza restaurants in the United States and internationally in Asia, the Middle East, Australia, Canada, Latin America and the Caribbean

Franchise.Name: Little Chef
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Little Chef is a chain of roadside restaurants in the United Kingdom, founded in 1958 by entrepreneur Sam Alper, and modelled on American diners.

Franchise.Name: Liva Pastanesi
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Turkish cake and desert shop

Franchise.Name: Livraria Bertrand
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Livraria Bertrand is the oldest and largest bookstore chain in Portugal

Franchise.Name: Livraria Cultura
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Livraria Cultura is a chain of bookstores in Brazil, founded in 1948 in São Paulo

Franchise.Name: LloydsPharmacy
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: LloydsPharmacy is a British pharmacy company, with more than 1,500 pharmacies.

Franchise.Name: London Drugs
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: London Drugs Ltd. is a Canadian retail store chain with headquarters in Richmond, British Columbia.

Franchise.Name: Long White Cafe
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Long White Cafe is open 24 hours and provides coffee, as well as a selection of hot and cold food.

Franchise.Name: Longchamp
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Longchamp is a French-owned family business in the business of selling luxury leather goods. Founded in 1948, Longchamp now operates 1,500 retail outlets across 80 countries in the world. The company’s products include its innovative “Le Pliage” women’s foldable handbag, which continues to be the company’s best selling products.

Franchise.Name: Longs Drugs
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Longs Drugs is an American chain with approximately 40 drugstores throughout the state of Hawaii.

Franchise.Name: Lotteria
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Lotteria is a chain of fast-food restaurants in East Asia that grew out of its first shop in Tokyo, Japan in September 1972.

Franchise.Name: Louis Vuitton
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Louis Vuitton Malletier, commonly referred to as Louis Vuitton, or shortened to LV, is a fashion house and luxury retail company founded in 1854 by Louis Vuitton.

Franchise.Name: MADO
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Turkish ice cream and desert chain

Franchise.Name: Mang Inasal
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Mang Inasal, is a barbecue fast food restaurant chain in the Philippines, established in Iloilo City in 2003.

Franchise.Name: Manhattan Fish Market
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Inspired by the famous Fulton Fish Market, Manhattan Fish Market is a restaurant chain serving American-style seafood such as the famous Manhattan Fish n’ Chips, the all-time favourite Garlic Herb Mussels and the legendary Manhattan Flaming Seafood Platter. Currently, Manhattan Fish Market is present in 72 countries around Asia and Middle East, with numerous industry awards under our belt.

Franchise.Name: Manner
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Josef Manner & Comp AG, an Austrian family business, unifies five of the best-known and well-liked confectionary brands. Our brands are associated with high quality and delicious taste. All products are manufactured exclusively at locations in Austria. We consider our label a promise to the people, which we aspire to fulfill every day.

Franchise.Name: Mannings
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Mannings is a chain of personal health and beauty retailer offering comprehensive range of pharmacies, healthcare, personal care, skin care and baby care products

Franchise.Name: Mario's Pizzeria
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Mario's Pizzeria is a pizza restaurant chain in Trinidad and Tobago.

Franchise.Name: Marmaris Büfe
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Since 1964, we are at your service with our warm, friendly environment and our known registered tastes to bring our brand to our country and the whole world.

Franchise.Name: Marrybrown
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Marrybrown is a Malaysian-based halal-certified fast food restaurant chain established in 1981. It was the first local fast food chain to franchise its business in Malaysia with more than 130 restaurants locally

Franchise.Name: Mary Brown's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Mary Brown’s Chicken & Taters, usually referred to as Mary Brown’s, is a Canadian quick service restaurant with approximately 140 locations coast-to-coast across Canada.

Franchise.Name: Massimo Dutti
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Massimo Dutti is a clothes manufacturing company that is part of the Inditex group. Although started as a men’s clothing company, the company now produces and markets women’s and children’s line, as well as perfumes.

Franchise.Name: Matsuya Foods
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Matsuya Foods is a Japanese major restaurant chain serving gyudon, other donburi, and curry.

Franchise.Name: MAX
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: MAX is Swedens oldest and most loved Hamburger Chain. Founded in 1968, the ambition is still the same today. With the best commosites we create the best hamburgers

Franchise.Name: Maxim's Caterers
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Maxim's Caterers Limited is a Hong Kong based food, beverage and restaurant chain 50% owned by Dairy Farm International Holdings Limited.

Franchise.Name: Max's of Manila
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Max's of Manila is a Philippine-based restaurant which serves fried chicken and other Filipino dishes. It is owned and operated by Max's Group, Incorporated.

Franchise.Name: McDonalds
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Today, McDonald's is one of the world's largest restaurant chains, serving approximately 69 million customers daily in over 100 countries across approximately 36,900 outlets as of 2016. McDonald's primarily sells hamburgers, cheeseburgers, chicken products, french fries, breakfast items, soft drinks, milkshakes, wraps, and desserts

Franchise.Name: McNally Robinson
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: McNally Robinson Booksellers is a family-operated chain of Canadian independent bookstores founded in Winnipeg, Manitoba in 1981.

Franchise.Name: MedPlus
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: MedPlus is an Indian pharmacy retailer headquartered in Hyderabad, India

Franchise.Name: Meijer
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Find low prices on all of your Grocery, Pharmacy, Gift Card, Electronics, Home, and Style essentials at Meijer.

Franchise.Name: Mercury Drug
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Mercury Drug is a pharmacy chain in the Philippines.

Franchise.Name: Metro
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Metro is an Icelandic fast food restaurant chain. It replaced McDonald's after McDonald's left Iceland in October 2009

Franchise.Name: Metropol
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Quality and trust in our working principles have always been our first priority. We have adopted the slogan of high quality products and affordable shopping. Thanksgiving documents that we have received in continuous audits have become a classic now.

Franchise.Name: Mexx
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Mexx is an international fashion company that designs clothes and accessories for men, women and children.

Franchise.Name: Michel's Patisserie
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Michel's Patisserie is an Australian founded and owned chain of bakery-style food outlets, that also operates internationally in New Zealand, Indonesia and China purveying cakes, pies, savouries, and espresso coffee.

Franchise.Name: Microsoft Store
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Microsoft Corporation is an American multinational technology company with headquarters in Redmond, Washington. It develops, manufactures, licenses, supports and sells computer software, consumer electronics, personal computers, and services.

Franchise.Name: Migros
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Migros is Switzerland's largest retail company, its largest supermarket chain and largest employer. It is also one of the forty largest retailers in the world.

Franchise.Name: Millie's Cookies
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Millie's Cookies is chain of retail bakeries based in the United Kingdom, specializing in cookies, muffins, hot drinks and gifts. It was named after its founder Mario Budwig's grandmother Mildred.

Franchise.Name: Mini Kalzone
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Mini Kalzone is the first Brazilian fast food chain specialised in calzone.

Franchise.Name: Mo'men
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Mo'men is a chain of fast foodrestaurants based in Cairo, Egypt, specializing in sandwiches. Mo'men is a wholly owned subsidiary of the Mo'men Group.

Franchise.Name: Montana Grill
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Montana Grill is a chain of Brazilian barbeque restaurants established some 20 years ago. Part of Halipar Group now, Montana Grill is present in almost 100 stores across Brazil.

Franchise.Name: Morley's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Morley's is a fast food chain based in the United Kingdom, selling fried chicken, burgers and spare ribs.

Franchise.Name: MOS Burger
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: MOS Burger is a fast-casual restaurant chain originated in Japan. It is now the second-largest fast-food franchise in Japan after McDonald’s Japan, and owns numerous overseas outlets over East Asia, including Taiwan, Singapore, Hong Kong, Thailand, Indonesia, Australia, and South Korea.

Franchise.Name: Mostaza
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Mostaza is an Argentinian fast food chain that was established in 1998. Its specialities are hamburgers, sandwiches, desserts and café.

Franchise.Name: MPH Group
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: MPH Group is a Malaysian group of companies best known for its book retailing and online retailing services as well as being involved in the printing, publishing and distribution of books and library services in Malaysia and Singapore.

Franchise.Name: Mr Bigg's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Mr Bigg's is one of Nigeria's fast food restaurants. Owned by conglomerate United African Company of Nigeria PLC, there are currently around 170 locations in Nigeria, including the country's first drive-throughrestaurant, with another four locations in Ghana.

Franchise.Name: Mr. Lee
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Mr. Lee is a popular fast-food chain in mainland China, specializing in beef noodle soup and other Chinese-style fast food. It is headquartered in Beijing

Franchise.Name: Mr. Sub
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Mr. Sub, originally called Mr.Submarine before the 1990s, is a Canadian chain of over 200 submarine sandwich shops.

Franchise.Name: Multivlaai
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: National pastry chain

Franchise.Name: Mu-Mu
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: For over 17 years in the market, MU-MU café chain has opened 40 cafés in Moscow and its international airports, stealing the hearts of millions of locals and guests of the capital of Russia.
