A delightful taste and high quality food, reasonable price and excellent customer service is what makes us proud, happy and pleased at MU-MU.

Franchise.Name: Mundo Verde
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: At the age of 30, Mundo Verde has established itself as a pioneer and leader in the proposal to develop and encourage the concept of healthy life through food in Latin America. Today Mundo Verde has over 400 stores all over Brazil and a varied product mix, which includes everything from food (diet, light, whole, organic, functional, gluten-free and lactose-free), food supplements and supplements for athletes.

Franchise.Name: Nacho King!
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Nacho King! is the largest Tex-Mex food manufacturer in the Philippines. It operates kiosk and food cart franchises in many marketplaces and malls in the major cities of the Philippines

Franchise.Name: Nando's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Nando's is an international casual dining restaurant chain originating in South Africa. Founded in 1987, Nando's operates about 1,000 outlets in 30 countries

Franchise.Name: Narecza
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Turkish pharmacy brand

Franchise.Name: National Book Store
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: National Book Store is a bookstore and office-supplies store chain based in the Philippines.

Franchise.Name: Nene Chicken
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Nene Chicken is a South Korean-based international fried chicken restaurant franchise.

Franchise.Name: Nespresso
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Nespresso is the brand name of Nestlé Nespresso S.A., an operating unit of the Nestlé Group, based in Lausanne, Switzerland

Franchise.Name: New York Fries
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: New York Fries is a Canadian quick service restaurant that mainly serves French fries and hot dogs. They also serve poutine.

Franchise.Name: New York Pizza
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The biggest pizza delivery chain in the Netherlands

Franchise.Name: Nirula's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Nirula's is India's oldest fast food restaurant chain. Based in North India and most popular in NCR Delhi, it was Delhi's first fast food restaurant, opening in Connaught Place in 1977.

Franchise.Name: Noodle Box
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Noodle Box Pty Ltd is an Australian stir fried noodle quick service restaurant chain headquartered in Melbourne, Victoria, Australia founded by Josh James and David Milne in 1996.

Franchise.Name: Nordsee
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Nordsee is a German fast-food restaurant chain specialising in seafood.

Franchise.Name: Number 8
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: A contemporary bar and cafe showcasing the best of New Zealand wines and beers.

Franchise.Name: O'Briens Irish Sandwich Bars
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: O'Briens Irish Sandwich Cafe, is an Irish franchise sandwich cafe chain founded in Ireland in 1988 by Brody Sweeney.

Franchise.Name: Odyssey
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Odyssey is a chain of bookstores in India, headquartered in Adyar, Chennai. Apart from books, the stores also sell music, movies, multimedia, stationery, toys and gifts.

Franchise.Name: Old Chang Kee
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Old Chang Kee had it humble beginnings in a small stall in 1956 Singapore, serving a local favorite of curry puff. Today, Old Chang Kee specializes in the production of high quality food, and in May 2017 The U.S based Travel & Leisure Magazine announced selected Old Chang Kee as one of the world’s 20 best fast food chains.

Franchise.Name: OldTown White Coffee
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: OldTown White Coffee is Malaysia’s largest halal-certified kopi tiam restaurant. The company also manufactures instant beverage mixes and products, in addition to operating over 237 café outlets throughout Malaysia and the region such as Singapore, China, Indonesia, and Australia.

Franchise.Name: OPEN 25HS!
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: OPEN 25HS! Is a drugstore developed from the concept of customer-first. Every OPEN 25HS! stores offer an unparalleled range of products and services that attract the public, where our staffs can server you with courtesy and make you feel comfortable.

Franchise.Name: Opmar Optik
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: pmar Optical stores; World famous brands offer the liking of Turkish consumers with "SELF SERVİS" system. With the "SELF SERVİS" service concept that is applied for the first time in Turkey, our customers are able to choose glasses as they are comfortable, free and they wish.

Franchise.Name: Oporto
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Oporto is an Australian fast food restaurant franchise with a Portuguese-theme. Oporto specialises in Portuguese style chicken and burgers. Oporto describes itself as a wholly owned Australian company.

Franchise.Name: Orange Julius
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Orange Julius is an American chain of fruit drink beverage stores. The eponymous beverage is a mixture of ice, orange juice, sweetener, milk, powdered egg whites and vanilla flavoring, similar to a morir soñando or orange Creamsicle.

Franchise.Name: P.F. Chang’s China Bistro
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: P. F. Chang’s China Bistro is an Asian-themed US casual dining restaurant chain founded in 1993 by Paul Fleming and Philip Chiang, and headquartered in Scottsdale, Arizona. The chain specializes in American Chinese cuisine, plus other Asian dishes. Employees describe the menu as “Asian flavors.” As of October 2017, P. F. Chang’s operated 208 restaurants in the United States and over 100 in international markets under licensee agreements.

Franchise.Name: Page One
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Page One is a bookstore chain and publisher founded in Singapore by Mark Tan

Franchise.Name: Pancake Parlour
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The Pancake Parlour is an Australian family-owned pancake restaurant chain, serving sweet and savoury pancakes and crepes with locations in Victoria and the ACT.

Franchise.Name: Panera Bread
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Panera Bread Company is an American chain of bakery-café fast casual restaurants in the United States and Canada

Franchise.Name: Panos
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Belgian sandwich chain

Franchise.Name: Papa John's Pizza
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Papa John's Pizza is an American restaurant franchise company. It runs the third largest take-out and pizza delivery restaurant chain in the United States, with headquarters in Jeffersontown, Kentucky

Franchise.Name: Paper Plus
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Paper Plus sells books, stationery, cards, magazines and giftware, while Office Spot focuses on home office and business supplies.

Franchise.Name: Pasaport Pizza
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: t was adopted by İzmir people in a short time with pizza produced with special technique and rich menus. Pasaport Pizza continues to serve in the Aegean Region, especially in the Mediterranean, Marmara, Central Anatolia, Black Sea and Eastern Anatolia regions, and continues to spread rapidly throughout Turkey.

Franchise.Name: Pasquale Hnos.
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Pasquale Hnos is a Peruvian chain of fast food restaurants founded by Gastón Acurio, Arnold Wu and Edwin Wu, that sells primarily Peruvian sanguches, chicha morada and Peruvian desserts

Franchise.Name: PAUL
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: 125 years old, PAUL is the Ambassador of the French art de vivre. Present in over 33 countries, the brand’s teams share the love of work well done, the joy of offering to our customers each day the very best quality products in a setting that is enchanting and unique

Franchise.Name: Peet's Coffee & Tea
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Peets offers approximately 30 types of freshly roasted whole beans and fresh in-store brewed coffee.

Franchise.Name: Pelita Nasi Kandar
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The Pelita Nasi Kandar is a famous and the largest Nasi Kandar restaurant chain in Malaysia. Its main headquarters is in Taman Chai Leng, Perai, Penang.

Franchise.Name: Penti
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Now our goal is to further strengthen our position in the socks market that we are the clear leader and to continue our leadership in underwear and swimwear retailing as well as in socks. Being a global brand from Turkey and becoming a "lovebrand" of women in Turkey as well as abroad.

Franchise.Name: Pepper Lunch
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Pepper Lunch is a international food franchise popularizing the concept of “fast-steak”. Pepper Lunch has opened numerous stores throughout the Asia Pacific region, serving steaks and chickens on top their signature electromagnetic cooker.

Franchise.Name: Pharmasave
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Pharmasave is a Canadian independent pharmacy and drugstore retailer with over 650 stores across Canada.

Franchise.Name: Piola
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: In 1986, in the heart of Treviso, Piola was founded to re-invent the pizzerias. The success achieved in Italy by Piola has started to spread around the world with franchised locations: the United States, Brazil, Argentina, Chile, Mexico, Turkey, Canada, Colombia and Ecuador.

Franchise.Name: Pit Stop
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Pit-Stop cafe network has gained respect and trust of its clients. Our mission is providing to our clients the dishes prepared from purely organic and ecologically safe products. We practice “open kitchen” principle so that our customers can be convinced of high quality and cooking conditions in the kitchen.

Franchise.Name: Pita Pit
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Pita Pit is a quick-service restaurant franchise serving pita sandwiches. Its headquarters are in Kingston, Ontario, Canada.

Franchise.Name: Pizza Express
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: PizzaExpress is a restaurant group with over 400 restaurants across the United Kingdom and 40 overseas in Europe, Hong Kong, India and the Middle East

Franchise.Name: Pizza Hut
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Pizza Hut is an American restaurant chain and international franchise founded in 1958 by Dan and Frank Carney. The company is known for its Italian-American cuisine menu including pizza and pasta, as well as side dishes and desserts

Franchise.Name: Pollo Campero
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Pollo Campero is a fast-food restaurant chain, located in Guatemala, El Salvador, Ecuador, Nicaragua, Mexico, Spain, Bahrain, the United States, and Italy.

Franchise.Name: Pollos Frisby
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Pollos Frisby is a Colombian fried chicken restaurant chain founded by Alfredo Hoyos Mazuera in 1983. Frisby was founded more than 35 years ago in Pereira.

Franchise.Name: Popeyes
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: A multinational fast food chain based out of New Orleans, Louisiana, Popeyes serves fried chicken and other Southern comforts. Today, it serves 40 states in America as well as 30 countries worldwide.

Franchise.Name: Popular Holdings
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Popular Holdings commonly called Popular, is a Singapore-based company that publishes, distributes, and retails Chinese and English language books.

Franchise.Name: Powell's Books
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Powell's Books is a chain of bookstores in Portland, Oregon, and its surrounding metropolitan area.

Franchise.Name: Pressbyrån
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Pressbyrån is a chain of Swedish convenience stores in Sweden that sells magazines and newspapers, convenience foods such as chilled drinks, potato chips, candy bars, ice cream, and hot dogs, and tobacco products.

Franchise.Name: Pret a Manger
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Cafe focussing on more healthier eating

Franchise.Name: Proxim
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Proxim is a Canadian group of pharmacists located in Quebec

Franchise.Name: Puket
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Puket was founded with the motto: just create products that we fall in love with! And this combination of joy with quality products and innovative design captivated not only Brazilians, but people around the world, now counting more than 6,000 national and international sales points, turning mania into countries like Angola, Bogotá, Bolivia, Dubai, Panama and Qatar, transmitting with joy and good humor all who come into contact with our products.

Franchise.Name: Queensland Book Depot
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Queensland Book Depot is a large chain of bookshops in Australia, with the majority of stores found in the states of Queensland and New South Wales.

Franchise.Name: Quick
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Quick Restaurants is an originally Belgian chain of hamburger fast food restaurants founded in 1971 by veteran Belgian entrepreneur Baron François Vaxelaire, Quick is the first hamburger chain founded in Europe with around 400 restaurants.

Franchise.Name: Quickly
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Since its founding in 1996, Quickly has grown to become the largest tapioca milk tea franchise in the world, with over 2000 stores around the globe. Branding itself as a New Generation Asian-Fusion style franchise, Quickly serves a daily concoction of bubble milk tea, frozen yogurt, and egg puffs.

Franchise.Name: Rahva Raamat
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Rahva Raamat is the largest retail and wholesale bookseller in Estonia.

Franchise.Name: Ráscal
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Ráscal is a chain of 12 restaurants serving dishes inspired by Mediterranean cuisine, with Italian influences and an emphasis on the richness and diversity of domestic ingredients. Ráscal doesn’t have a central kitchen. Each restaurants produces the food that it serves, from pizza dough to fresh sauces, every day. We include different recipes in the menu every week, keeping true to our DNA and to gastronomic trends of each season – and, of course, always celebrating our classics.

Franchise.Name: Ray Ban
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Luxury sunglasses

Franchise.Name: Red Ribbon Bakeshop
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Red Ribbon Bakeshop, is a Philippine food company which maintains a fast-food and bakery chain under the trade name "Red Ribbon".

Franchise.Name: Red Rooster
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Red Rooster is an Australian and New Zealand fast food restaurant chain founded in 1972 that specialises in roast chicken. Their product range includes whole roasts, half roasts, wraps, burgers, fish related products, salads, beverages and desserts.

Franchise.Name: Rei do Mate
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Rei do Mate is a Brazilian fast food chain of tea house stores.

Franchise.Name: Relay
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Relay is a chain of newspaper, magazine, book, and convenience stores, mostly based in train stations and airports. It is owned by Lagardère Travel Retail, a subsidiary of Lagardère Group.

Franchise.Name: Remzi Kitabevi
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Remzi Kitabevi has been the pioneer of cultural publishing for 90 years and at the same time offers foreign books as well as Turkish books through a widespread bookstore network.

Franchise.Name: Renaud-Bray
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Renaud-Bray is the largest chain of French-language bookstores in North America

Franchise.Name: Rex Bookstore
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Rex Bookstore, Inc. (RBSI) is an educational book publisher and bookstore chain in the Philippines.

Franchise.Name: Rexall
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Rexall is a chain of American drugstores, and the name of their store-branded products.

Franchise.Name: Rite Aid
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Rite Aid Corporation is a drugstore chain in the United States and a Fortune 500 company. It is headquartered in Camp Hill, East Pennsboro Township, Cumberland County, Pennsylvania

Franchise.Name: Rituals
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: They are everywhere: at any given moment, of every single day, waiting to be discovered, eager to share the beauty within them. They are the seemingly meaningless moments we all tend to overlook. Rituals unveils these moments and reminds you to experience them with joy. Whether it’s taking a nice long bath or creating a homey atmosphere with the rich scent of Asian incense, Rituals allows you to find happiness in the smallest of things.

Franchise.Name: Robin's Donuts
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Robin's Donuts is a Canadian chain of 140 doughnut shops that operates in every province of Canada except Quebec.[1][2] Its operations are run by the Afton Food Group.

Franchise.Name: Rodilla
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Rodilla is a Madrid, Spain-based restaurant chain that specializes in cold and hot sandwiches, salads, pastries and fried dishes for dining in or take-out.

Franchise.Name: Rolex
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Rolex SA is a Swiss luxury watchmaker. The company and its subsidiary Montres Tudor SA design, manufacture, distribute and service wristwatches sold under the Rolex and Tudor brands.

Franchise.Name: Rolls
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Rolls is a Finnish chain of hamburger fast food restaurants. Founded in 1988, the company has around one hundred restaurants throughout the country.

Franchise.Name: Rossmann Türkiye
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Rossmann decided to invest in Turkey in 2009, and by August 2017 reached 79 stores in Turkey. Rossmann continues to be in the process of becoming a store by targeting the centers of various cities and continues to invest in Turkey without slowing down.

Franchise.Name: Rotiboy
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Rotiboy is a Malaysian bakery chain based in Kuala Lumpur owned by Rotiboy Bakeshoppe Sdn Bhd.

Franchise.Name: Royal Castle
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Royal Castle is a fast food restaurant chain in Trinidad and Tobago.

Franchise.Name: Saat&Saat
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: A Turkish watch brand.

Franchise.Name: Sakae Sushi
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Sakae Sushi is a restaurant chain based in Singapore serving Japanese cuisine.

Franchise.Name: Sakura Sushi Bar
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: A full selection of Japanese cuisine handmade by our chef, covering appetizers, soups and salads, sushi, noodles, rolls and bento boxes.

Franchise.Name: Salvatore Ferragamo
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Salvatore Ferragamo S.p.A. is an Italian luxury goods company, with headquarters in Florence, specializing in shoes, leather goods, and ready-to-wear for men and women.

Franchise.Name: Sam's Chicken
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Sam's Chicken is a British fast food chain. It has 34 outlets, the majority of which are in west and north west London.

Franchise.Name: Samsonite
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Samsonite International S.A. is an American luggage manufacturer and retailer, with products ranging from large suitcases to small toiletries bags and briefcases.

Franchise.Name: Samsung
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Samsung Group is a South Korean multinational conglomerate headquartered in Samsung Town, Seoul. It comprises numerous affiliated businesses, most of them united under the Samsung brand, and is the largest South Korean chaebol.

Franchise.Name: Sanborns Bookstore
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Grupo Sanborns is a large restaurant, retail, pharmacy and department store chain located in Mexico, El Salvador and Panama.

Franchise.Name: Sanborns Pharmacy
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Grupo Sanborns is a large restaurant, retail, pharmacy and department store chain located in Mexico, El Salvador and Panama.

Franchise.Name: Saravana Bhavan
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Saravana Bhavan is one of the largest vegetarian restaurant chains in the world, founded in 1981 offering south Indian Vegetarian cuisine.

Franchise.Name: Sate Kajang Haji Samuri
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Sate Kajang Haji Samuri is a Sate Kajang fast-food restaurant chain in Malaysia. The main headquarters is located in Medan Sate, Kajang, Selangor.

Franchise.Name: Sbarro
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Sbarro, LLC is a chain of pizzeria that specializes in New York style pizza by the slice and other Italian-American cuisine.

Franchise.Name: Schuler Books & Music
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Schuler Books & Music, formerly known as simply Schuler Books, is a small Michigan chain of bookstores. Along with books, DVDs, and music CDs, the stores sell food and beverages at in-store cafes.

Franchise.Name: SCR Express
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: SCR is a Malaysian halal-certified chicken rice fast-food restaurant in Sarawak.

Franchise.Name: Segafredo Zanetti Espresso
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The Segafredo Zanetti Espresso brand was born thanks to the great and passionate work of an Italian coffee merchant, Mr. Massimo Zanetti. Descendant from a family with more than two generations in the coffee trade business, Mr. Zanetti launched the first Segafredo Café back in 1988 in Paris. Today the Segafredo Zanetti Espresso brand is a global network of Italian Cafe.

Franchise.Name: Seven & I
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: is a Japanese diversified retail group headquartered in Nibancho, Chiyoda, Tokyo, Japan. Seven & I was founded in 1920 as Ito-Yokado, and is now the fifth largest retailer in the world, with 54,000 stores in approximately 100 countries

Franchise.Name: Shaurma №1
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Shaurma, a fast food restaurant and cafe chain, is proud to be the first nation-wide name in the fast food industry. For several years now, we have made national delicacies for a quality and healthy food, providing our customers with a whole range of high-quality services.

Franchise.Name: Shokoladnitsa
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Shokoladnitsa is one of the largest and oldest chains of coffee shops in Russia, with over 420 outlets around the country. It dates back to the legendary café on Oktyabrskaya metro station opened in 1964, the only one café recognized in the capital for several decades and famous for gourmet delicacies and drinks such as hot chocolate.

Franchise.Name: Shoppers Drug Mart
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Shoppers Drug Mart Corporation is a Canadian retail pharmacychain based in Toronto, Ontario.

Franchise.Name: Shoppers Stop
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Shoppers Stop outlets retail clothing, accessories, handbags, shoes, jewellery, fragrances, cosmetics, health and beauty products, home furnishing and decor products

Franchise.Name: Sibylla
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Sibylla is a chain of fast food restaurants available throughout Sweden and Finland, where they mostly hold the concession for service station food serveries.

Franchise.Name: Simit Sarayı
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Turkish pastry and snack shop

Franchise.Name: Skyteam Lounge
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Not really a restaurant, a buiness lounge available to any person flying premium class on an airline that is part of skyteam

Franchise.Name: Smokin'Joe's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: A tribute to the love-lorn Mexican who made pizzas a celebration of fine taste

Franchise.Name: ŞOK
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: ŞOK Marketler T.A.Ş., which has over 74 stores and more than 4500 stores, continues to work to ensure that every customer who enters stores is satisfied with the tasteful, high quality and affordable shopping experience.

Franchise.Name: Soobe
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: At Soobe we have combined fun, moderation and creativity, we want to create a world where children between 0-12 years will find their own style and express themselves

Franchise.Name: South Bar & Cafe
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: A contemporary bar and cafe showcasing the best of New Zealand wines and beers.

Franchise.Name: South Star Drug
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: South Star Drug is a chain of drugstores in the Philippines. It was established in 1937 as a small business venture engaged in the retail of Chinese herbal medicines, located in Naga City, Philippines.

Franchise.Name: Southern Fried Chicken
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Southern Fried Chicken is a British-based fast food outlet. It operates a franchise network in the United Kingdom and worldwide.

Franchise.Name: SPAR International
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: SPAR is the world’s leading voluntary food retail chain. The business started with one Dutch store in 1932 and now comprises more than 12,500 stores in 44 countries on four continents. The development of SPAR has been underpinned by a set of values that have guided the organisation since its establishment more than 80 years ago.

Franchise.Name: Spoleto
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Spoleto is a Brazilian restaurant chain that develops the concept of fast food to Italian cuisine.

Franchise.Name: Sportive
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Sportive is Turkey's leading multi-brand sports retail chain, reinforcing its sectoral experience with innovations and open-minded visions. It is Turkey's leading sports retail chain serving 32 stores in 19 cities and sales area of ​​27,000 square meters.

Franchise.Name: Spudulike
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Spudulike is a restaurant chain and franchise specialising in baked potatoes (potatoes being known as "spuds" in colloquial British English) that first opened in Edinburgh in 1974. Spudulike purveys baked potatoes with various fillings, other potato-based meals, and side dishes.

Franchise.Name: Spur Steak Ranches
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Spur Corporation is a steakhouse franchise restaurant chain originating from South Africa.

Franchise.Name: Square Pie
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Square Pie is a British food retail chain based in Hackney, east London, which specialises in handmade pies.

Franchise.Name: Starbucks
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: American coffee shop

Franchise.Name: Stardogs
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Stardogs specializes in selling high-quality hot hot dogs and sandwiches from quality materials. Our food is prepared according to the quality standards with modern equipment, which complete all the outlets, in compliance with the strictest sanitary requirements.

Franchise.Name: Steers
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Steers is one of South Africa’s most recognizable quick-service restaurantbrands. The company is well known for serving flame-grilled burgers made from 100% pure beef and handmade chips.

Franchise.Name: Stefans Käsekuchen
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Stefans Käsekuchen (Stefans Cheesecake) bakes daily fresh creamy cheesecake with love, craftsmanship and ingredients from the region! The recipe is their big secret, but one thing is certain and they are happy to tell you that only the best will come in. They sell individual cheese cake variations (e.g. classic or with fine fruity raisins) and seasonal recommendations such as cheesecake with fine poppy seeds, juicy cherries, orange tangerine, delicious blueberries, fine german plums, apricots or rhubarb from the region.

Franchise.Name: Steimatzky
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Steimatzky is the oldest and largest bookstore chain in Israel.

Franchise.Name: Subway
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: American sandwish shop

Franchise.Name: SugarBun
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Established in 1979, we have grown from a humble ice cream parlour into an innovative Food and Beverage Franchise Restaurant Brand. With monumental presence in Sarawak (East Malaysia) (even in rural towns such as Mukah, Kapit and Saratok), we have moved into international markets successfully - Brunei Darussalam, Bangladesh, Australia and Indonesia.

Franchise.Name: Sukiya
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Sukiya is the largest chain of gyudon(beef bowl) restaurant. Sukiya has 1964 restaurants throughout all 47 Japanese prefectures as of 2017, as well as 70 in China

Franchise.Name: Sumo Salad
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Sumo Salad is an Australian salad bar that founded in 2003 in Liverpool Street, Sydney Sydney by Luke Baylis and James Miller.

Franchise.Name: Suomalainen Kirjakauppa
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Suomalainen Kirjakauppa (meaning 'Finnish bookshop') is the largest bookshop chain in Finland, with its flagship branch in Helsinki being Finland's largest bookshop.

Franchise.Name: Superdrug
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Superdrug is a health and beauty retailer in the United Kingdom

Franchise.Name: Supermac's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Supermac’s is an Irish fast food restaurant chain first opened in 1978. The first restaurant was located in Ballinasloe Town, County Galway in the West of Ireland.

Franchise.Name: Super-Pharm
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Super-Pharm is a pharmacy chain in Israel.

Franchise.Name: Swarovski
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Swarovski designs, manufactures and markets crystals, genuine gemstones & created stones and finished products such as jewelry and accessories, beauty products, and lighting. Our diverse product portfolio also incorporates precision optical instruments such as telescopes and binoculars, grinding, drilling and sawing tools, and industrial lighting. Other activities include Swarovski Entertainment, the company’s film division, which collaborates with exceptional talent and industry partners to develop, finance, and produce original and artistically accomplished feature films, Swarovski Kristallwelten, a dazzling interactive crystal experience in Wattens, Austria, and the Swarovski Crystal Society and publications and apps, that illuminate the many different facets of the Swarovski business

Franchise.Name: Swedish Gift Shop
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Swedish Gift Shop has items from the most renowned Swedish glassworks such as Kosta Boda, Orrefors and Målerås. You’ll also find an assortment of other souvenirs and toys made in Sweden that will bring happiness to people of all ages.
Franchise.Notes: Not to be confused with "The Swedish Gift Shop"

Franchise.Name: Taco Bell
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: American fastfood chain

Franchise.Name: Tansaş
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Tansaş is a chain of supermarkets serving in Turkey.

Franchise.Name: Tantalizers
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Tantalizers is a leading Nigerian fast food restaurant chain.

Franchise.Name: Tastee Fried Chicken
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Tastee Fried Chicken is a fast food fried chicken restaurant based in Victoria Island, Lagos, Nigeria.

Franchise.Name: Tattered Cover
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Tattered Cover is a bookstore chain in Denver, Colorado. It is one of the largest independent bookstores in the United States.

Franchise.Name: Tavuk Dünyası
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Tavuk Dünyası brand has been developed by TD Food Services, which has been operating since 2003 in the food and beverage sector and currently has more than 70 restaurants and cafes serving in 5 countries and 30 cities.

Franchise.Name: Teknosa
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: TeknoSA A.Ş, electronic goods retail chain. It was established on July 25, 2000.

Franchise.Name: Teremok
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Teremok is a popular fast food chain in Russia that specialises in Russian crepes (blini).

Franchise.Name: Texas Chicken
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Church’s Chicken, also known as Texas Chicken outside the United States, is the 3rd largest chicken restaurant chain in the world. Texas Chicken operates 1,700 stores across 25 countries, serving fried chicken, fries, and biscuits.

Franchise.Name: TGI Fridays
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: As the original casual dining bar and grill, TGI Fridays offers authentic American food and legendary drinks, served with genuine personal service. Bringing people together to socialize and celebrate the freeing and liberating spirit of “Friday” was the concept’s founding premise, from which the brand promise “In Here, It’s Always Friday” was born.

Franchise.Name: Thalia
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Thalia is a chain of more than 200 book shops in Germany (a country with fixed book prices), Austria and Switzerland.

Franchise.Name: The Belgian Chocolate House
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The Belgian Chocolate House is an initiative of the International Duty Free. Today, with more than 800 tons of chocolate sold each year in Zaventem, The Belgian Chocolate House offers three sorts of confectionery: pralines, chocolates, biscuits. The Belgian Chocolate House is the largest sales point of chocolate worldwide: 1.4 kg per minute, 24/7.

Franchise.Name: The Chicken Rice Shop
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The Chicken Rice Shop is a company incorporated in Malaysia, which was established in June 2000. The Chicken Rice Shop is a chicken rice fast-food restaurantand Halal family restaurant chain in Malaysia.

Franchise.Name: The Coffee Bean & Tea Leaf
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Business description: The Coffee Bean & Tea Leaf, often shortened as Coffee Bean, is an American coffee chain headquartered in Los Angeles. Serving fine roasted beans and hand-brewed tea leaves from Camarillo, Coffee Bean is present in 32 countries with the bulk of its operation focused in Asia.

Franchise.Name: The Coffee Club
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The Coffee Club has a real focus on quality, you can enjoy anything from a range of hot, freshly prepared breakfasts to light and main meals, gourmet salads and snacks.

Franchise.Name: The Keg
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The Keg is a Canadian chain of steakhouse restaurants and bars located in Canada and the United States.

Franchise.Name: The West Cornwall Pasty Company
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The West Cornwall Pasty Company is a fast food chain in the United Kingdom specialising in making and selling pasties. The company's headquarters are in Long Crendon, Buckinghamshire, while its products are manufactured in Penryn, Cornwall.

Franchise.Name: The Works
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The Works is a discount retailer based in the UK selling an extensive range of books, art and craft materials, gifts, toys, games and stationery. It has over 400 stores across the UK and Ireland.

Franchise.Name: Tim Hortons
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Canadian fastfood chain

Franchise.Name: Titan
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Owned by the Tata Group, one of the leading names in watches and jewellery, through its sub-brands Titan Watches, Sonata, Fastrack, Tanishq Jewellery

Franchise.Name: TKK Fried Chicken
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: TKK Fried Chicken is a Taiwanese chain of fried chicken restaurants. Outside its Taiwan locations, TKK also has branches in China.

Franchise.Name: Tokyo Tokyo
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Tokyo Tokyo is a Japanese fast food restaurant chain in the Philippines.

Franchise.Name: Tong Tji
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Tong Tji is a family-owned business out of Indonesia in the field of tea manufacturing and retail. The company operate numerous store chains throughout Indonesia and is recognized as a leading brand in the country.

Franchise.Name: Tortilla
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Tortilla is a fast food restaurant chain based in the United Kingdom. Brandon and Jennifer Stephens from California founded Tortilla in London in 2007.

Franchise.Name: Toys R us
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Toys "R" Us, Inc. is an American toy and juvenile-products retailer founded in 1948 and headquartered in Wayne, New Jersey, in the New York City metropolitan area.

Franchise.Name: Travelex
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Travelex Group is a foreign exchange company founded by Lloyd Dorfman and headquartered in London. Its main businesses are international payments, bureaux de change and issuing prepaid credit cards for use by travellers. It is the world's largest foreign exchange bureau

Franchise.Name: TWG Tea
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: TWG Tea is one of the finest luxury tea brands in the world, with presence in across the globe. TWG Tea’s collection – the largest in the world – numbers well over 800 different single-estate, fine harvests and exclusive tea blends from all of the tea-producing countries.

Franchise.Name: Tzomet Sfarim
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Tzomet Sfarim is the second largest bookstore chain in Israel,

Franchise.Name: Underground Coffee Company
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: The team at Underground Coffee Company is committed to producing the perfect espresso for the discerning consumer, along with a delicious selection of freshly baked items and prepared meals.

Franchise.Name: Upper Crust
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Baked throughout the day and famous for our freshness, we are THE baguette specialists.

Franchise.Name: Vaango
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Literally meaning 'Come in', 'Vaango' is the quintessential Tamilian way of welcoming guests. Said with a gentle forward bob of the head, a smile and a folded-palm namaskaar, it is the gateway to the magical handiwork of masterchefs of South of India who have made their cuisine amongst the truly greats of our time.

Franchise.Name: Vadilal
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Vadilal Industries Ltd is India’s second largest ice cream player. The company is also one of the largest processed food players in India with significant exports of frozen vegetables and ready to eat snacks, curries and breads.

Franchise.Name: Valters un Rapa
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Valters un Rapa is a bookstore and publishing house in Riga, Latvia.

Franchise.Name: Value Drug Mart
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Value Drug Mart is a Western Canada drug store serving over 35 locations throughout Alberta and British Columbia.

Franchise.Name: Vatan Computer
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Turkish electronic device salesman

Franchise.Name: Victorinox
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: World renowned for its quality, Victorinox is a leading manufacturer of pocket knives and time pieces

Franchise.Name: Vitusapotek
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Vitusapotek is a chain of 200 pharmacies in Norway owned and run by Norsk Medisinaldepot, a subsidiary of the German company Celesio AG.

Franchise.Name: Wagamama
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Japanese cuisine.

Franchise.Name: Waitrose
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Waitrose is a chain of British supermarkets, which forms the food retail division of Britain's largest employee-owned retailer, the John Lewis Partnership. Its head office is located in Bracknell, Berkshire, England

Franchise.Name: Walgreens
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Walgreens) is an American company that operates as the second-largest pharmacy store chain in the United States

Franchise.Name: Wasa Crystal
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Wasa Crystal is a family business that has grown from one small shop to six store locations in Stockholm and Oslo. Wasa Crystal features the finest Swedish crystal art, exceptional crystal wares and outstanding customer service.

Franchise.Name: Wasabi
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Wasabi is a fast food restaurant chain based in the United Kingdom, focused on Japanese food, especially sushi and bento, and operating in London and New York.

Franchise.Name: Waterstones
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Waterstone's, is a British book retailer that operates about 250 stores, mainly in the UK, also other nearby countries.

Franchise.Name: Watsons
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Watsons is the largest health care and beauty care chain store in Asia.

Franchise.Name: Wayne's Coffee
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Welcome to the world of Wayne's Coffee! Our aim is to offer our guests the most natural meeting place and an assortment of high-quality products. Come to Wayne's Coffee - you will notice the difference between us and every other coffee shop you have ever visited.

Franchise.Name: Well Pharmacy
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Well is the largest independent pharmacy business

Franchise.Name: Wendy's
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: American fastfood chain

Franchise.Name: Wetherspoons
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: British bar serving food and drink

Franchise.Name: Whitcoulls
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Whitcoulls is a major national bookstore, stationery, gift, games & toy store chain in New Zealand

Franchise.Name: White Spot
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: White Spot is a Canadian restaurant chain based in Vancouver, British Columbia, best known for its hamburgers, Pirate Pak children's meal and burger sauce. Some locations have carhop service.

Franchise.Name: Whole Foods
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Whole Foods Market Inc. is an American supermarket chain exclusively featuring foods without artificial preservatives, colors, flavors, sweeteners, and hydrogenated fats

Franchise.Name: WHSmith
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: WHSmith is a British retailer, headquartered in Swindon, Wiltshire, which operates a chain of high street, railway station, airport, port, hospital and motorway service station shops selling books, stationery, magazines, newspapers and entertainment products

Franchise.Name: Wienerwald
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Wienerwald is a German franchise chain of fast-food restaurants with stores in Germany, Turkey, Egypt, Hungary, United Arab Emirates and Romania specializing in Hendl, Schnitzel, and other chicken products. Its name means Vienna Woods.

Franchise.Name: Wishbone
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Fresh food made with 100% love by professional chefs every day.

Franchise.Name: World Duty Free
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: World Duty Free SpA, the holding company of World Duty Free Group, is an Italy-based multinational travel retailer

Franchise.Name: Wow! Momo
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Wow! Momo is a chain of fast food restaurants headquartered in Kolkata, specializing in Momos, a dumpling popular in Nepal and parts of Tibet and India.

Franchise.Name: Xinhua Bookstore
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Xinhua Bookstore owns the largest and only country-wide bookstore chain in China.

Franchise.Name: Xocolat
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Xocolat is one of Vienna’s first specialist shops for connoisseurs of the cocoa bean, and they’ve got their radars switched on for any new bleeps in the chocolate galaxy. The golden rule is no preservatives and only the best beans, and chocolate aficionados will find acclaimed international brands and local brands alike.

Franchise.Name: Xurcun
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Xurcun provides its client who have an eye for food and give preference to the quality with delicacies and dried fruits with great history, brought from different points of the world and selected with special attention. Today Xurcun reminds us of pleasant moments of the past, but also opens window to the future.

Franchise.Name: Ya Kun Kaya Toast
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Ya Kun Kaya Toast is a Singaporean chain of mass-market, retro-ambience cafes selling toast products, soft-boiled eggs, and coffee. From humble beginnings at a small stand in 1944, Ya Kun today is a recognized Singaporean icon present in Asia Pacific.

Franchise.Name: Yo Sushi!
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Sparklingly fresh Japanese food comes thick and fast at this pioneering conveyor-belt sushi chain. Perch at the counter and grab the passing colour-coded plates or pick from hot and cold dishes on the menu.

Franchise.Name: Yogen Früz
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Yogen Früz is a Canadian chain of frozen yogurt and smoothie stores that also serves healthy alternative food products. The chain is run through company-owned, franchised, and non-traditional partnerships.

Franchise.Name: Yoshinoya
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Yoshinoya is the 2nd largest gyudon restaurant chain in Japan, serving various affordable Japanese delicacies like beef bowls and miso soup. Yoshinoya also operates a chain of stores in the United States, Hong Kong, Cambodia, China, Indonesia, Malaysia, Philippines, Singapore, Taiwan and Thailand.

Franchise.Name: Zalatimo
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: It all began in Jerusalem in the year 1860 when our great grandfather, Mohammed Zalatimo created a unique kind of sweets he named Mutabbaq, using the finest hand picked ingredients. Today, our family carry on our grandparents’ tradition of making the famous Mutabbaq using the original unique recipe, as well as other favoured Arabic and Western pastries. Our products embody the pride and dedication of true tradition carried on over generations.
Franchise.CEO: Ahmed Zalatimo and Talal Wael Zalatimo

Franchise.Name: Zalatimo Sweets
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Zalatimo Sweets Company established itself in Amman, Jordan in 1986 with a mission to create and sell high quality gourmet products offering value for money with excellent customer service. Each of our tasty creations are produced consistently while keeping in focus the original, fresh hand-made taste the company is known for.Today, the company has been expanding both locally and regionally. Currently, there are twelve retail outlets in Jordan, in addition to a branch in Kuwait.

Franchise.Name: Zara
Franchise.Author: Community
Franchise.Description: Zara is a Spanish clothing and accessories retailer based in Arteixo, Galicia. The company was founded in 1975 by Amancio Ortega and Rosalía Mera.
